51.2	Devaluation	Devaluation	Devaluation is a reduction in the value of a currency with respect to those goods, services or other monetary units with which that currency can be exchanged.‘Devaluation’ means official lowering of the value of a country's currency within a fixed exchange rate system, by which the monetary authority formally sets a new fixed rate with respect to a foreign reference currency. In contrast, depreciation is used for the unofficial decrease in the exchange rate in a floating exchange rate system. Under the second system central banks maintain the rates up or down by buying or selling foreign currency, usually USD.	
